{"add":{"doc":{"id":"ee44778cdc82ae03eaa3d396176cfa19cdb38b0154a498590c91136ad6675bbb","url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/e/eb/OrwellBurmaPassport.jpg/170px-OrwellBurmaPassport.jpg","previous":[],"after":["Blair's maternal grandmother lived at Moulmein, so he chose a posting in Burma. In October 1922 he sailed on board SS Herefordshire via the Suez Canal and Ceylon to join the Indian Imperial Police in Burma. A month later, he arrived at Rangoon and travelled to the police training school in Mandalay. After a short posting at Maymyo, Burma's principal hill station, he was posted to the frontier outpost of Myaungmya in the Irrawaddy Delta at the beginning of 1924."]}}}